Configuring your browser's parameters

   You may refuse to accept cookies by activating the setting on your
   browser that allows you to block the setting of all or some cookies.
   Unless you have adjusted your browser setting so that it will refuse
   cookies, our system will issue cookies as soon as you visit the
   website. If you have blocked all or some cookies, it is possible that
   the website will no longer function correctly or that you will not have
   access to some parts of the site, for which we cannot be held liable.

How to opt out of cookies and targeted advertising (ad retargeting)

   Opting out of cookies and targeted advertising

   To opt out of retargeted ads on Google, please refer to Google's help
   article: https://support.google.com/ads/answer/2662922?hl=en-GB

   To block Google Analytics tracking in your browser, you can install
   this Google Analytics opt-out browser add-on:
   https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout/

   You can find out more information about how to opt out of interest
   based advertising at these links: www.networkadvertising.org/choices
   www.aboutads.info/choices

   Disabling cookies In your browser

   You may be able to disable cookies by using your browser settings. We
   have included information below for some commonly used web browsers:

   https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95647

   https://support.microsoft.com/en-gb/help/17442/windows-internet-explore
   r-delete-manage-cookies

   https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/enable-and-disable-cookies-website
   -preferences

   You may also be able to use Incognito browsing mode, if your browser
   offers the functionality, which may prevent some cookies from being
   saved to your device.

   Updates to the cookies policy

   We reserve the right to make any changes to this policy, particularly
   in response to legislative requirements.

   To exercise your right to query, access and amend your personal data,
   you can contact us by email at privacy.lh@lafargeholcim.com

